_ftn8"></a><a href="#_ftnref8">[8]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> R. Stevens, ‘Government and the Judiciary’, in V. Bogda</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">nor (ed), </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">The British Constitution in the Twentieth Century</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> (Oxford: Oxford University Press, 2003), p.346.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn9"></a><a href="#_ftnref9">[9]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> T. Poole and S. Shah, ‘The Impact of the Human Rights Act on the House of Lords’ [2009] PL 347, 361.  See also: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">The Supreme Court Annual Report an</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">d Accounts 2010-2011</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> (London: The Stationery Office, 2011), HC 976, p.6.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn10"></a><a href="#_ftnref10">[10]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> Lord Phillips, Gresham Lecture, 2 June 2010.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn11"></a><a href="#_ftnref11">[11]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">R</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> v. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Secretary of State for Transport, ex parte Factortame (No.2) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">[1991] 1 AC 603. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn12"></a><a href="#_ftnref12">[12]</a><span style="font-family:'Times N